com.tailf.conf

Class ConfTypeDescriptor

  • Object
    • com.tailf.conf.ConfObject
      • com.tailf.conf.ConfTypeDescriptor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable

    public class ConfTypeDescriptor
extends ConfObject
    Conf value type descriptor. This class is used to represent the type of an arbitrary Conf value. It also contains helper methods to create ConfValue classes from String representations *

    Example: 

     ConfTypeDescriptor typeDesc = new ConfTypeDescriptor(ConfObject.J_BUF);
 ConfBuf buf = (ConfBuf) typeDesc.newInstance("Hello");
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
